Hello, I get the following error when parsing this function:

```
namespace Company { namespace Product {
  template <typename T> class ClassName : private ClassName_Base<T>
  {
    ClassName(T value, enum Company::Product::Communication::ChannelStatus::ECStatus status, OtherProduct::DateTime_t timestamp)
  };
} } // namespaces
```

```
WARNING: Error when parsing function declaration:
If no return type {
Invalid definition: Expected identifier in nested name, got keyword: enum [error at 44]
  Company::Product::ClassName::ClassName(T value, enum Company::Product::Communication::ChannelStatus::ECStatus status, OtherProduct::DateTime_t timestamp)
  ----------------------------------------------------^
} else if return type {
If declId, parameters, and qualifiers {
Invalid definition: Expected identifier in nested name. [error at 30]
  Company::Product::ClassName::ClassName(T value, enum Company::Product::Communication::ChannelStatus::ECStatus status, OtherProduct::DateTime_t timestamp)
  --------------------------------------^
} else If parenthesis in noptr-declarator {
Invalid definition: Expecting "(" in parameters_and_qualifiers. [error at 33]
  Company::Product::ClassName::ClassName(T value, enum Company::Product::Communication::ChannelStatus::ECStatus status, OtherProduct::DateTime_t timestamp)
  -----------------------------------------^
}
```

If I change the function signature in the code to 

`ClassName(T value, OtherProduct::Int32_t status, OtherProduct::DateTime_t timestamp)`
the errors are gone, so it maybe has to do with the enum type?

I have Sphinx Version 1.3.1 and Breathe 4.1.0 installed. 
I also tried with sphinx commit [c9470fa...](https://github.com/sphinx-doc/sphinx/commit/c9470fac65b999dd3289c6c93e5192fc1bb1cca0), where a similar issue was fixed, as well as the latest master branch, but I get the same error with all versions.

Any Ideas why this happens? Is it a Sphinx or a Breathe issue? Thanks for your time and for making this great software!

