I believe the deis builder is failing to fetch the latest version of the scxml submodule, leaving stale node_modules. I have seen this happen in other projects.

I've tried to set Heroku's NODE_MODULES_CACHE=false, but I'm not sure whether this is supported by deis: https://devcenter.heroku.com/articles/nodejs-support#cache-behavior

The only workaround I have found is to delete the module in package.json, and then re-add it. This forces the builder to download the correct module. However, this requires two distinct pushes to deis, doubling build time, and leaves bogus commits in my git history, so it's not an ideal solution.

Hello, I am writing a function which yields results. It seems backoff.on_exception does not work with yield keyword.

@backoff.on_exception(
  backoff.expo, (ConnectionError, ConnectTimeout), max_tries=MAX_RETRIES)
def fib():
  for i in range(1, 10):
    raise ConnectionError
    yield i

It seems after the generator is generated, it will not go to the retry logic again. Is there any way to fix this?

Hello, I'm facing with a problem:
```
Could not load file or assembly 'System.Net.Http, Version=4.2.0.0, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=b03f5f7f11d50a3a'. The system cannot find the file specified.
```
when trying to interact with HttpClient inside net core library, which is loaded as dynamic library with AssemblyLoader
```
var loader = new AssemblyLoader();
var assembly = loader.LoadFromAssemblyPath(Path.Combine(providersFolder, assemblyName));
var type = assembly.GetType(fullClassName);
var paymentProvider = Activator.CreateInstance(type) as IPaymentProvider;
```

Library source:
```
public class FirstPaymentProvider: IPaymentProvider
    {
        public PaymentStates ProcessPayment(string operatorExternalId, string paymentParams, long paymentAmount, ILogger logger)
        {
            var result = PaymentStates.Error;

            var request = new StringBuilder("http://test.com/api?");

            try
            {
                var requestParams = JObject.Parse(paymentParams);
                foreach (var requestParam in requestParams)
                {
                    request.Append($"{requestParam.Key}={requestParam.Value}&");
                }
               
                if(request[request.Length - 1] == '&')
                    request.Remove(request.Length - 1, 1);
            }
            catch (Exception ex)
            {
                logger.LogError($"PaymentProvider Exception : {ex.Message}, on parsing paymentParams : {paymentParams}");
                return result;
            }

            try
            {
                var client = new HttpClient();
                client.DefaultRequestHeaders.Accept.Clear();
                var responseMessage = client.GetAsync(request.ToString()).Result;
                if (responseMessage.StatusCode == HttpStatusCode.OK)
                {
                    var str = responseMessage.Content.ReadAsStringAsync().Result;
                    logger.LogInformation($"Response is : {str}");
                    result = PaymentStates.Successful;
                }
                else
                {
                    result = PaymentStates.Processing;
                }
            }
            catch (Exception ex)
            {
                logger.LogError($"PaymentProvider Exception on request : {ex.Message}");
                return result;
            }

            return result;
        }       
    }
```

